Entrance to Addington hospital situated on South Beach, Durban was built in 1879. It was named after R. Hon. Henry Addington, Prime Minister of Great Britain in 1801. March 22, 2013. DURBAN - Workers at the Addington Hospital in Durban are refusing to work. This is because lifts are not working. READ: Addington Hospital accused of hiding COVID-19 cases Patients and staff are now forced to use stairs to get to wards, some of which are 10 storeys high. Staff say that they have been reporting the matter for years. READ: COVID-19: Hospitalised patients want to go home They blame the poor conditions on a lack of maintenance. Health MEC, Nomagugu Simelani-Zulu announced the possibility of relocating the hospital in October.